>Where exactly is the ground for the starter?  it is
>just grounded to the tranny, which is grounded by the
>wire that goes from the nose of the tranny to the body
>of the bus.

Yes, the tranny ground strap is actually a flat woven copper band.

My bus also has an auxilliary strap from the starter to the battery ground bolt in the engine compartment.

>the only other thing I can think of is
